|rad2oui = |rad2_ant_conn = RP-SMA |rad2txchains = 2 |rad2rxchains = 2 |rad2sstreams = 2 |rad2stand = IEEE 802.11a/n |rad2n = 300 |rad2a = 54 |rad2freq = 5 |rad2correv = |rad2cap = }}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== Per Rosewill, this device uses a '''Broadcom''' SoC (says BCM5358), has 8MB Flash, and has 64MB RAM.
Per the manual, the device uses BCM5358U (presumed B0 rev.) and BCM43236. However, the manual states the device has 32MB RAM.. Per the manual, the default SSIDs are '''RW-2.4G-XXX''' and '''RW-5G-XXX'''. The MAC label on the board in the FCC internal photos may have an OUI of 00:1F:A4 ('''Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics'''). :There are some entries for the '''RX-2.4G-XXX''' pattern on '''WiGLE''' (all '''RW-2.4G-001'''). There is a single '''RW-5G-001''' entry as well, but the BSSID may be bogus... ==Links of Interest== [http://rosewill.com/products/2292/ProductDetail_Overview.htm Product page]
